tablet preserved"},{"kind":"text","text":"] from the devils and from the alteration of anything thereof: (Jel:) or, accord. to one reading,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHofuwZN","text_ar":"مَحْفُوظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", this epithet being thus made to relate to the Kur-án. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates, and then as a subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A young child;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the dial. of Mekkeh; as a term of good omen: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAfiyZu","text_ar":"مَحَافِيظُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Kept,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retained, in the mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"memory; known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"learned, by heart."},{"kind":"text","text":"Hence the phrase,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraDa maHofuwZaAtihi EalaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"عَرَضَ مَحْفُوظَاتِهِ عَلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He showed the things which he kept,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retained, in his mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"memory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which he knew,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had learned, by heart, to such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Jel"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}